  "author": "ByteByteGo",
  "siteName": "ByteByteGo Newsletter",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div dir=\"auto\" class=\"body markup\">\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\"><br></h2>\n   <p>This week’s system design refresher:</p>\n   <ul>\n    <li>\n     <p>The Generative AI Tech Stack</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>24 Good Resources to Learn Software Architecture in 2025</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>ByteByteGo Technical Interview Prep Kit</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Database Index Types Every Developer Should Know</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>The Agentic AI Learning Roadmap</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>12 MCP Servers You Can Use in 2025</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>SPONSOR US</p></li>\n   </ul>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!fnkm!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4739f8fe-ff86-4567-a4b5-9c6f177a6198_2360x2664.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/47b892b6-778d-4458-55ad-f2006355e400/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"1644\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4739f8fe-ff86-4567-a4b5-9c6f177a6198_2360x2664.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1644,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:498221,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/167925185?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4739f8fe-ff86-4567-a4b5-9c6f177a6198_2360x2664.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>GenAI refers to systems capable of creating new content, such as text, images, code, or music, by learning patterns from existing data. Here are the key building blocks for GenAI Tech Stack:</p>\n   <ol>\n    <li>\n     <p>Cloud Hosting &amp; Inference: Providers like AWS, GCP, Azure, and Nvidia offer the infrastructure to run and scale AI workloads.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Foundational Models: Core LLMs (such as GPT, Claude, Mistral, Llama, Gemini, Deepseek) trained on massive data, form the base for all GenAI applications.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Frameworks: Tools like LangChain, PyTorch, and Hugging Face help build, deploy, and integrate models into apps.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Databases and Orchestration: Vector DBs (such as Pinecone, Weaviate), orchestration tools (such as LangChain, LlamaIndex) manage memory, retrieval, and logic flow.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Fine-Tuning: Platforms like Weights &amp; Biases, OctoML, and Hugging Face enable training models for specific tasks or domains.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Embeddings and Labeling: Services like Cohere, Scale AI, Nomic, and JinaAI help generate and label vector representations to power search and RAG systems.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Synthetic Data: Tools like Gretel, Tonic AI, and Mostly AI create artificial datasets to enhance training.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Model Supervision: Monitor model performance, bias, and behavior. Tools such as Fiddler, Helicone, and WhyLabs help.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Model Safety: Helps ensure ethical, secure, and safe deployment of GenAI systems. Solutions like LLM Guard, Arthur AI, and Garak help with this.</p></li>\n   </ol>\n   <p>Over to you: What else will you add to this list?</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\"><a href=\"https://bit.ly/Moov_071225\" rel=\"\">How Top Fintech Engineering Teams Actually Ship (Sponsored)</a>\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/167925185/how-top-fintech-engineering-teams-actually-ship-sponsored\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://bit.ly/Moov_071225\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a0c86143-b88f-4bd8-301e-039ec8399600/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"764\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/cae9885d-246c-4fe6-bd48-22cd4c523684_1600x840.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:764,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:994613,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://bit.ly/Moov_071225&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/167919491?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcae9885d-246c-4fe6-bd48-22cd4c523684_1600x840.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p><strong>fintech_devcon</strong><span> is the technical conference where real builders share how they ship complex systems at scale.</span></p>\n   <p>Hear directly from engineers at Amazon, Block, Plaid, Chime, DocuSign, Gusto, and more.</p>\n   <p>Topics include:</p>\n   <p><span> 💸Ledgers + payment infra</span><br><span> 🔐 Onboarding, auth, and security</span><br><span> 🧠 LLMs + fraud detection</span><br><span> 🧰 Dev tooling + API design</span><br><span> 💥 No sales pitches; just architecture diagrams, code, and battle scars</span></p>\n   <p>This is where fintech’s toughest engineering challenges get unpacked.</p>\n   <p>It’s all happening August 4–6 in Denver.</p>\n   <p><span>🎟️ Use </span><strong>BBG25</strong><span> to save $195.</span></p>\n   <p data-attrs=\"{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://bit.ly/Moov_071225&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Get your ticket&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}\" data-component-name=\"ButtonCreateButton\" class=\"button-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://bit.ly/Moov_071225\" rel=\"\" class=\"button primary button-wrapper\"><span>Get your ticket</span></a></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">24 Good Resources to Learn Software Architecture in 2025 \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/167925185/good-resources-to-learn-software-architecture-in\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!aA_-!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3ce6d9b9-a475-4096-80dd-8015a60caf02_2360x2952.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/bfd900d1-7685-4941-f627-d667a4eaba00/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"1821\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/3ce6d9b9-a475-4096-80dd-8015a60caf02_2360x2952.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1821,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"Image\" title=\"Image\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>The resources can be divided into different types such as:</p>\n   <ol>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Software Design Books</span><br><span>Some books that can help are DDIA, System Design Volume 1 &amp; 2, Clean Architecture, Domain-Driven Design, and Software Architecture: the Hard Parts</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Tech Blogs and Newsletters</span><br><span>Read technical blogs by companies like Netflix, Uber, Meta, and Airbnb. Also, the ByteByteGo newsletter provides insights into software design every week.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>YouTube Channels and Architectural Resources</span><br><span>YouTube channels like MIT Distributed Systems, Goto Conferences, and ByteByteGo can help with software architecture and system design. Azure Architecture Center and AWS Architecture Blog are other important resources.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>WhitePapers</span><br><span>For deeper insights, read whitepapers like Facebook Memcache Scaling, Cassandra, Amazon DynamoDB, Kafka, and Google File System.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Software Career Books</span><br><span>A Software Architect also needs to develop holistic skills. Books about software career aspects such as Pragmatic Programmer, The Software Architect Elevator, The Software Engineer's Guidebook, and Philosophy of Software Design can help.</span></p></li>\n   </ol>\n   <p>Over to you: Which other resources will you add to the list?</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">ByteByteGo Technical Interview Prep Kit \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/167925185/bytebytego-technical-interview-prep-kit\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p><span>Launching the All-in-one interview prep. We’re making all the books available on the </span><a href=\"https://bytebytego.com/\" rel=\"\">ByteByteGo website</a><span>.</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://bytebytego.com/\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/6a785d6e-d888-44d5-fc09-b7d47b82ef00/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"2061\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/f836cb42-7734-4a14-8e10-a1f7a8efaac0_4406x6238.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:2061,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:5493101,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://bytebytego.com/&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/167542144?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff836cb42-7734-4a14-8e10-a1f7a8efaac0_4406x6238.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>What's included:</p>\n   <ul>\n    <li>\n     <p>System Design Interview</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Coding Interview Patterns</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Object-Oriented Design Interview</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>How to Write a Good Resume</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Behavioral Interview (coming soon)</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Machine Learning System Design Interview</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Generative AI System Design Interview</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Mobile System Design Interview</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>And more to come</p></li>\n   </ul>\n   <p data-attrs=\"{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://bytebytego.com/&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Launch sale: 50% off&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}\" data-component-name=\"ButtonCreateButton\" class=\"button-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://bytebytego.com/\" rel=\"\" class=\"button primary button-wrapper\"><span>Launch sale: 50% off</span></a></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Database Index Types Every Developer Should Know \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/167925185/database-index-types-every-developer-should-know\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!L8Xa!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f3238dc-99de-4c6a-a3e3-f1cbfe4dae2a_2360x2770.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/fca89a25-03ff-45f4-1031-28a1c0a86100/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"1709\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/9f3238dc-99de-4c6a-a3e3-f1cbfe4dae2a_2360x2770.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1709,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"Image\" title=\"Image\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>A database index is a derived structure that maps column values to the physical locations of rows in a table. Let’s look at some key index types:</p>\n   <ol>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Primary Index</span><br><span>This index is automatically created when a primary key is defined on a table. Such an index can be dense as well as sparse, though sparse is preferred in most scenarios.</span></p>\n     <p>A dense index contains one entry for every row in the table. On the other hand, a sparse index contains entries for only some rows in the table.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Clustered Index</span><br><span>A clustered index determines the physical order of rows in a table. Only one clustered index can exist on a table because data can only be stored in one order at a time. It is great for range queries, ordered scans, and I/O efficiency.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Secondary Index</span><br><span>A non-clustered index is a separate structure that holds a copy of one or more columns along with pointers to the actual rows in the table. It doesn’t affect how data is physically stored, and it can use the primary index to locate the records.</span></p></li>\n   </ol>\n   <p>Over to you: Which other index type will you add to the list?</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">The Agentic AI Learning Roadmap \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/167925185/the-agentic-ai-learning-roadmap\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!f6k3!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4c66f381-6232-4745-933c-82b76ecfb6a2_2250x2952.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/21686e7e-9749-4a52-af24-544e1b29cb00/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"1910\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4c66f381-6232-4745-933c-82b76ecfb6a2_2250x2952.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1910,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"Image\" title=\"Image\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <ol>\n    <li>\n     <p>An AI Agent is a system capable of autonomous actions, reacting to its environment, using tools (APIs, Internet, code, etc), and can work under human guidance.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p>To build AI agents, one must know tools like Python, Jupyter, PyTorch, and GitHub Copilot. These enable coding, experimentation, and integration with AI libraries and APIs.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>GenAI Foundational Models</span><br><span>Familiarity with large models like GPT, Gemini, LLaMa, DeepSeek, and Claude is essential. These models provide the base intelligence that agents can use for reasoning, generation, and understanding.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>AI Agent Development Stack</span><br><span>Tools like Langchain, AutoGen, Crew AI, and frameworks like Semantic Kernel and Hugging Face power agent workflows. These components manage tasks, memory, and external tool integrations in agent pipelines.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>API Design</span><br><span>Understanding API design approaches like REST, GraphQL, gRPC, and SOAP is crucial to building interoperable agents. Key concepts include HTTP methods, status codes, versioning, cookies, headers, and caching.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Type of AI Agents</span><br><span>Learn about the several types of AI agents, such as simple reflex, model-based reflex, goal-based, utility-based, and learning agents. Each varies in complexity.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>AI Agent System Architecture</span><br><span>AI agents can operate as single agents, in multi-agent systems, or in human-machine collaboration. Architecture depends on the use case.</span></p></li>\n   </ol>\n   <p>Over to you: What else will you add to the AI Agent Learning Roadmap?</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">12 MCP Servers You Can Use in 2025 \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/167925185/mcp-servers-you-can-use-in\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!cqt7!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2192842c-bdbc-4b1c-bf45-36a9d4b9a450_1280x1546.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/6b4c747c-3929-4ca2-2837-ceda3a808200/public\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1546\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2192842c-bdbc-4b1c-bf45-36a9d4b9a450_1280x1546.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1546,&quot;width&quot;:1280,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;No alternative text description for this image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"No alternative text description for this image\" title=\"No alternative text description for this image\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>MCP (Model Context Protocol) is an open standard that simplifies how AI models, particularly LLMs, interact with external data sources, tools, and services. An MCP server acts as a bridge between these AI models and external tools. Here are the top MCP servers:</p>\n   <ol>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>File System MCP Server</span><br><span>Allows the LLM to directly access the local file system to read, write, and create directories.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span> GitHub MCP Server</span><br><span>Connects Claude to GitHub repos and allows file updates, code searching.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Slack MCP Server</span><br><span>MCP Server for Slack API, enabling Claude to interact with Slack workspaces.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Google Maps MCP Server</span><br><span>MCP Server for Google Maps API.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Docker MCP Server</span><br><span>Integrate with Docker to manage containers, images, volumes, and networks.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Brave MCP Server</span><br><span>Web and local search using Brave’s Search API.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>PostgreSQL MCP Server</span><br><span>An MCP server that enables LLM to inspect database schemas and execute read-only queries.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Google Drive MCP Server</span><br><span>An MCP server that integrates with Google Drive to allow reading and searching over files.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Redis MCP Server</span><br><span>MCP Server that provides access to Redis databases.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Notion MCP Server</span><br><span>This project implements an MCP server for the Notion API.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Stripe MCP Server</span><br><span>MCP Server to interact with the Stripe API.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Perplexity MCP Server</span><br><span>An MCP Server that connects to Perplexity’s Sonar API for real-time search.</span></p></li>\n   </ol>\n   <p>Over to you: Which other MCP Server will you add to the list?</p>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "这篇 ByteByteGo 技术通讯对多个关键技术主题进行了简要概述，包括生成式 AI 技术栈、软件架构学习资源、数据库索引类型、AI 代理开发和模型上下文协议 (MCP) 服务器。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "这篇 ByteByteGo 技术通讯对多个关键技术主题进行了简要概述，包括生成式 AI 技术栈、软件架构学习资源、数据库索引类型、AI 代理开发和模型上下文协议 (MCP) 服务器。",
  "summary": "这篇 ByteByteGo 技术通讯汇编了多个技术领域的简要见解。它详细介绍了生成式 AI 技术栈的基本构建块，涵盖了从云托管和基础模型到微调、监督和安全解决方案的九个关键领域。该技术通讯还提供了一份精选的 24 个软件架构学习资源列表，对基本数据库索引类型（主索引、聚集索引、二级索引）进行了分类，概述了 AI 代理的开发路线图，并介绍了 12 个模型上下文协议 (MCP) 服务器的示例。内容的大部分是 ByteByteGo 面试准备工具包的赞助广告和产品推广。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "生成式 AI 系统依赖于多层技术栈。",
      "explanation": "这个综合生态系统包括基础设施、基础模型、框架、数据库、微调、嵌入、合成数据、监督和安全工具，对于构建和运营高级 AI 应用程序至关重要。"
    },
    {
      "point": "软件架构和 AI 代理的持续学习至关重要。",
      "explanation": "开发人员可以利用书籍、博客、YouTube 频道和白皮书等各种资源进行软件架构学习，而 AI 代理开发需要了解工具、基础模型、API 设计和各种代理类型。"
    },
    {
      "point": "数据库索引对于性能至关重要，而 MCP 等新协议则增强了 AI 交互能力。",
      "explanation": "理解主索引、聚集索引和二级索引类型对于数据库优化至关重要。此外，模型上下文协议 (MCP) 通过专用服务器简化了 AI 模型与外部数据和服务的交互方式，从而实现了更广泛的 AI 应用程序。"
    }
  ],
  "keyQuotes": [
    "生成式人工智能（GenAI）指的是能够通过学习现有数据的模式来创建新内容（例如文本、图像、代码或音乐）的系统。",
    "数据库索引是一种派生结构，它将列值映射到表中行的物理位置。",
    "AI 代理是一个能够自主行动、对其环境做出反应、使用工具（API、互联网、代码等）并在人工指导下工作的系统。",
    "MCP（模型上下文协议）是一种开放标准，它简化了 AI 模型（尤其是 LLM）与外部数据源、工具和服务的交互方式。"
  ],
